  "read": "TileLang selected-K-chunk grouped-D sparse-MLA backward dKV producer. It consumes real q/dO/output/lse plus compressed KV and packed group ids, recomputes P and scaled dP once for one block_k selected chunk, reuses those values across one or more D blocks, then reduces into a chunk-local active compressed-group table before final [groups, D] dKV atomics. This is the concrete smaller-accumulator follow-up to the full-panel grouped-D prototype that exceeded MI350 LDS limits at useful shapes. This run feeds real TorchTitan sparse-MLA boundary tensors into the TileLang dKV producer. Materialized per-head probs and scaled grad_logits are present only for materialized-input modes or correctness-reference checks; recompute mode uses q/dO/output/lse/compressed KV in the timed producer.",
